This new medium has other resources and other competitors, so the new population will have to, to be a strong competitor, to have other features or adaptations compared to those they needed before.
The original population has not changed, they need the same adaptations as before.
With the passing of time, while the new population starts adapting to their new environment, they begin to look less and less similar to the other population.
At the end, with the passing of thousands or even millions of years, the two populations will look so different that they cannot be called the same species.
We call this process to speciation, which simply means the formation of new species. Specification is an uneven consequence and a very important part of development.
